# Pantry Chef - API Keys & Environment Variables
# ⚠️  IMPORTANT: NEVER commit this file to GitHub!
# This file is listed in .gitignore and should stay local only.

# =============================================================================
# 1. SUPABASE (Database)
# =============================================================================
# Get these from: https://supabase.com → Your Project → Settings → API
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project-id.supabase.co
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your_supabase_anon_key_here

# =============================================================================
# 2. SPOONACULAR (Recipe API)
# =============================================================================
# Get this from: https://spoonacular.com/food-api → Dashboard
# Free tier: 150 calls/day
SPOONACULAR_API_KEY=your_spoonacular_api_key_here

# =============================================================================
# 3. EDAMAM (Nutrition API)
# =============================================================================
# Get these from: https://developer.edamam.com → Create App
# Free tier: 10,000 calls/month
EDAMAM_APP_ID=your_edamam_app_id
EDAMAM_APP_KEY=your_edamam_app_key

# =============================================================================
# SECURITY CHECKLIST
# =============================================================================
# ✅ This file is in .gitignore (won't be committed)
# ✅ Keep this file on your local machine only
# ✅ Don't share these keys in chat/email
# ✅ If keys are exposed, regenerate them immediately
# ✅ Use different keys for dev vs production

# =============================================================================
# HOW TO USE
# =============================================================================
# 1. Copy this file: cp .env.local.example .env.local
# 2. Fill in your actual API keys above
# 3. Save the file
# 4. Restart your dev server: npm run dev
# 5. Keys will be automatically loaded

# =============================================================================
# VERCEL DEPLOYMENT
# =============================================================================
# When deploying to Vercel, add these same keys in:
# Vercel Dashboard → Project → Settings → Environment Variables
# This keeps keys secure and separate from your code
